Canada appeals against bail for Omar Khadr, youngest ever Guantanamo prisoner
fulltext: The Canadian government is launching a last-ditch legal attempt to stop the youngest person ever detained at Guantanamo Bay from being released for the first time since he was 15 years old. At a court hearing in Edmonton on Tuesday , lawyers for Stephen Harper’s Conservative government will seek an emergency stay of a judge’s decision to grant bail to Omar Khadr, a 28-year-old Canadian citizen, who has spent nearly half his life behind bars.
